Hello Latonya,
 
Thank you for contacting Netwrix Technical Support. My name is Frantz, and I will assist you with this issue.
To help us streamline the troubleshooting process and resolve your issue more efficiently, please provide the following information:
 
Did you notice any error message from the DLP job?
 
What software is currently installed - run this command from an admin Powershell prompt:
 Get-CimInstance -Class Win32_Product |Where-Object {($_.Name -Like "Stealth*" -or $_.Name -like "Netwrix*" -or $_.Name -like "Postg*" -or ` $_.Name -like "Python*")} -ErrorAction SilentlyContinue

Thank you for your time today.
In today's meeting, we reviewed StealthAUDIT, and this covered the SEEK System Scan erring out because Sensitive Data was not installed.
We downloaded and installed the Sensitive data. You will run the SEK System Scan and the Bulk Import before you run the DLP.
You can reply to this email to provide an update.
 
Thanks,
